Align=3D"top">=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>What began as a conflict ov=
er the transfer of consciousness from flesh to machines escalated=
 into a war which has decimated a million worlds.<SPAN style=3D"m=
so-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The Core and the Arm have all but=
 exhausted the resources of a galaxy in their struggle for domina=
tion. Both sides now crippled beyond repair, the remnants of thei=
r armies continue to battle in new Galaxies, their hatred fueled=20=
by over four thousand years of total war. </P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNo=
rmal><O:P></O:P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>This is a fight to th=
e death. For each side, the only acceptable outcome is the comple=
te elimination of the other.</P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal><O:P></O:=
P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>In the far future the galaxy is rul=
ed by a benevolent central body of humans and artificial intellig=
ences called the Core (a contraction of "Consciousness Repository=
"). The Core's technological and economic triumphs have allowed h=
umanity to colonize most of the Milky Way and enjoy peace and pro=
sperity. <SPAN style=3D"mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>However,=
 the balance is broken by a technological breakthrough which allo=
ws the consciousness of a human being to be reliably transferred=20=
into a machine, thereby granting theoretically indefinite life in=
 a process called "patterning". </P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal><O:P>=
</O:P></P>=0A<P class=3DMsoNormal>To counter patterning, the Arm=20=
resorted to cloning their best warriors. Now after thousands of y=
ears there are a few thousand "originals" only.<SPAN style=3D"mso=
-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Entirely human, but cloned into gen=
etic stagnation, the Arm exibit biases close to Human ones.<SPAN=20=
style=3D"mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Their hated rivals, the=20=
Core, will be eliminated on sight. Recently gated into a new Gala=
xy, The Arm will quickly try and seek out the Core.</P></TD></TR>=
